    <p>
        <strong>1. Why scorpdb has been created?</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
        This database is designed to help researchers and increase research in the field of scorpions. In this database, we intend to collect all the information of protein and nucleotide sequences of Iranian scorpions and provide them to researchers for public use.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>2. Is information about other venomous animals published on this site?</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
        No, this site is only for scorpions, especially Iranian scorpions.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>3. Can the authors use the information published in this database for use in their studies?
    </strong>
    </p>
    <p>
        Yes, by mentioning the reference, all the information of this database is open to the public.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>4. How to cite scorpdb?
    </strong>
    </p>
    <p>
        If you find Scorpdb helpful, please consider citing Scorpdb via the link below:
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="http://scorpdb.com/">https://www.scorpdb.com</a>
    </p>
    <p>
        or please consider citing the publications that published the protein sequences used in your work.
    </p>
